cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CC 

This paper is primarily focused on data stream algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses information theory concepts such as Shannon entropy, which suggests a possible fit for cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of stable random projections and sample complexity analysis suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on compressed counting and estimation techniques could also fit under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
